cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its findings, please cite it as below."
title: "neural-cdma: Engineered Superposition in Pretrained LLMs — a forensic activation-watermark system and an empirical map of the non-linear wall"
abstract: >-
  A white-box activation-watermarking system for forensic provenance and legal
  non-repudiation of LLM generations, together with an empirical study of where
  engineered CDMA superposition collapses on off-the-shelf pretrained models.
  The central finding: CDMA superposition survives only in the linear channel
  or with a trained de-multiplexer, and every untrained non-linear readout
  collapses it; per-token surprise predicts multiplexability and language's
  per-token demand collapses the multiplexing capacity to K≈2.
type: software
